Notes:

Please follow the guide to execute the script. Some information is 
given in the data downloading and preprocessing. 

# Downloading the dataset of furniture (243.8MB)

Please have a look at the furniture datasets at Kaggle. 

https://www.kaggle.com/akkithetechie/furniture-detector


# Processing the data

Process use the following script dataset into the three sets including 
train, val and test with the give ratio such as 8:1:1 or any ratio that 
you want. 

## Install the data-splitting library
$ pip install split-folders

## Run the script for splitting the dataset 
$ split_folders.py


# tf.data

The class of tf.data is dedicated to build TensorFlow input pipelines 
randomly. For tf.data, please take the following weblink for reference.

https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/data


# Script and Modifications 
It is based on the scripts provided by Krishnendu. I would like to thank 
him for his contribution. Make the necessary changes to make the script 
run successfully and adapt to the environment of CUDA Toolkit 11.0, cuDNN 
8.0.1 and CUDA 450.57.


